burn.t.sol
├── when the call is a delegate call
│  └── it should revert
└── when the call is not a delegate call
   ├── when the stream is null
   │  └── it should revert
   ├── when the stream is active
   │  └── it should revert
   └── when the stream is either canceled or depleted
      ├── when the caller is unauthorized
      │  └── it should revert
      └── when the caller is authorized
         ├── when NFT is non-existent
         │  └── it should revert
         ├── when NFT exists
            ├── when the caller is an approved operator
            │  └── it should burn the NFT
            └── when the caller is the owner of the NFT
               └── it should burn the NFT
